                  <msItem>
                     <p> 
                        <persName>
                           <forename>Herbert</forename> de <surname>Burgherse</surname>
                        </persName> grants to <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> the sompner (sumonitori} of <placeName role="person" key="place_102097">Leawes</placeName>
                        </persName>, for
                  his service, 12 acres of land in the marsh of <placeName key="place_102068">Heilesham</placeName>, paying annually for the
                  same the third part of one half-mark, and at Christmas, the third part of one pound of pepper
                  and one pound of cummin. For this donation the said Richard gave 23 marks of silver, (<origDate notBefore="1220" notAfter="1230">c. 1220-30</origDate>.) 
                  . </p>
